  "usagePatterns": {
    "theme-variant-icons": "Each theme variant (cp, vp, ppm, maconomy) has its own predefined icon set and section structure. CP has 2 sections (lines 42-66), while VP, PPM, and Maconomy have 1 section each with identical icons currently. The appropriate variant is shown via CSS based on html theme class (lines 342-365). Custom sections override all theme defaults when provided.",
    "custom-icon-support": "Navigation items support two icon approaches: standard Icon component (icon: 'icon-name') or custom images (isCustom: true, customSrc: '/path/to/image.svg'). Custom images are rendered as <img> tags (lines 179, 216, 252, 288) with class left-sidebar__custom-icon, while standard icons use the Icon component. For custom images, set both isCustom and customSrc properties.",
    "panel-data-attributes": "Items use data attributes to control ShellPanel behavior when clicked: panelTitle (defaults to label), panelIcon (defaults to item icon), panelContentId (optional content identifier), and useGradientHeader (boolean, auto-applied for Dela AI). The sidebar script (lines 369-526) reads these attributes and dynamically updates the associated ShellPanel header and content.",
    "active-state-management": "The sidebar manages two types of active states: class-based (left-sidebar__item--active) for initially active items, and data-attribute-based (data-active) for runtime panel interactions. When a panel is opened, the script clears class-based active states and sets data-active on the clicked item (lines 483-489). This prevents conflicts between static and dynamic active states."
  },
